**1 Project Scope and Usage Scenario**

Basic usage for Aesthetix will be administrators who can access the database of images and create sets to be presented to adult users. The image sets will be presented with a question, which will provide direction on how the users are to rate the images in each set. The administrators will then be able to collect the rating data for all the image sets to be analyzed.

User groups: 

\-	admin (creates image database, questions, reviews collected answers)

\-	adult respondent (views image sets and responds to presented questions)

**2 Proposed Solution**

Our project is an open-source web application that curates and compares images through user interaction, where users select the most aesthetically pleasing image from sets of two or more. Leveraging this crowdsourced input, the system logs responses and produces detailed reports on image preferences. The standout feature we will implement is our incorporation of advanced algorithms—one generating image sets for comparison and another that can autonomously assess and rank the aesthetic value of images using machine learning or heuristic methods. We will also try to present this web application on a website that in itself is aesthetically pleasing and will encourage users to participate in rating images.

Our value proposition lies in the combination of user-driven evaluation and algorithmic insight, offering a dual approach to understanding aesthetics. Compared to others, our application emphasizes flexibility and customization, allowing it to be adapted for other media (e.g., sounds, text, code). This versatility, combined with its open-source nature, empowers users and developers alike to extend and refine the system.

**3 Use Cases**

*![][image1]*

**Use Case 1: Admin sets up image sets with questions**

• Primary actor: Administrator

• Description: Creating Image sets to be rated by Adult User

• Precondition: The user must have an administrator role and be logged into the system.

• Postcondition: A set of images is ready to be presented to users for ratings.

• Main Scenario:

1\. Administrator accesses image database

2\. Administrator selects images to group into pairs, triplets, or sets

3\. Administrator creates questions to accompany image sets

4\. Image sets and their questions are saved to the image rating database

5\. Notifications are sent to the administrator that the image sets and questions are ready to be presented to the user

• Extensions:

1\. Image groups are not saved to the database successfully. Administrator is notified via error message.

**Use Case 2: Admin collects rating data to review**

• Primary actor: Administrator

• Description: Image ratings are collected to be analyzed

• Precondition: The user must have an administrator role and be logged into the system.

• Postcondition: Image rating data is able to be exported for analysis and review

• Main Scenario

1\. Administrator accesses image rating database

2\. Administrator selects images to collect ratings data from

3\. Administrator clicks button to export data

4\. Data is exported to selected file time. (csv)

5\. Administrator logs out of system

• Extensions

1\. Error occurs while trying to export data. Administrator is notified data failed to export.

**Use Case 3: User rates images**

• Primary actor: Adult User

• Description: Image sets are presented to user to be rated

• Precondition: The user must have a login to access the image sets

• Postcondition: Image ratings are successfully added to the database

• Main Scenario

1\. User logs into system

2\. A set of images with an accompanying question is presented on the screen

3\. User provides a rating (1-10) for each image based on conditions described in the question

4\. User receives confirmation that ratings have been saved successfully.

5\. User logs out after completing ratings for all presented image sets

• Extensions

1\.  Image fails to load.

**Non-Functional Requirements:**

1\. **Performance:**

The system should handle simultaneous user ratings and admin actions without significant delay.

**Test Case**: Simulate multiple users rating images concurrently to ensure no performance bottlenecks.

2\. **Security:**

Only authorized administrators can modify the image database and export data. Users need login access.

**Test Case:** Attempt unauthorized access and verify that it is denied.

3\. **Usability:**

The system should be intuitive for both users and administrators, ensuring a smooth user experience.

**Test Case:** Conduct manual usability testing by asking users to navigate and rate images.

4\. **Scalability:**

The system should scale to accommodate a growing number of users and images.

Test Case: Increase the number of images and users to ensure the system remains responsive.

5\. **Reliability:**

The system should consistently save user ratings and admin modifications without data loss.

Test Case: Simulate network interruptions and ensure data integrity is maintained.
